  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ACCESS TO QUALITY EDUCATION WITH FOCUS ON KARAMOJA INCREASE ACCESS &amp; RETENTION IN POST PRIMARY EDUC</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Better access and completion of quality education in marginalised areas, with focus on Karamoja</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support is given to UNICEF as the lead agency working with 3 CSOs 7 District Local Governments of Karamoja and Ministry of Education and Sports Gender Technical Unit to provide an effective and efficient well-resourced formal quality education &amp; training system that is inclusive, relevant and accessible to all boys and girls with increased school retention, completion and achievement rates in Karamoja through evidence-based advocacy, institutional capacity building, communication, partnerships and innovations. (Addressing issues through three main components; Quality Education, Gender in Education and Violence against children in schools)</narrative>
  </description>
